ActCustoms Tariff
SubjectCPTPP Rules of Origin for Casual Goods Regulations
PrecisCPTPP RULES OF ORIGIN FOR CASUAL GOODS REGULATIONS are designed to implement, in Canada, the rules of origin negotiated by Canada and the COMPREHENSIVE AND PROGRESSIVE AGREEMENT FOR TRANS-PACIFIC PARTNERSHIP signatories that will be used to determine when goods have undergone sufficient production to qualify for preferential tariff treatment.
